Executive Profile
Spencer C. Fleischer  President, Co-Chief Executive Officer, Principal, and Managing Partner, FFL Partners, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships63--
Background

		Mr. Spencer C. Fleischer serves as the President, Co-Chief Executive Officer, Principal and Managing Partner at FFL Partners LP. Mr. Fleischer serves as President, Co-Chief Executive Officer, Principal and Managing Partner at Friedman Fleischer & Lowe Capital Partners III, L.P. He co-founded Friedman Fleischer & Lowe, LLC in 1997. Mr. Fleischer served as an Investment Banker and Manager at Morgan Stanley & Company for 19 years. He was responsible for substantial business ... units within the Investment Banking Division. Mr. Fleischer served as the Head of Investment Banking in Asia, the Head of Corporate Finance for Europe, the Head of United Kingdom Corporate Finance, the Head of Investment Banking and the Head of Corporate Finance at Morgan Stanley. He is Chairman of the Board of Transtar Holding Company. Mr. Fleischer served as the Chairman of Milestone AV Technologies, Inc. since September 2007. He serves as a Director of SKBHC Holdings LLC, Strategic Investment Group, Americans for Oxford, Inc., Chief Manufacturing Inc., and Chief Sanus Audio Visual. He has been a Director of Levi Strauss & Co. since July 11, 2013 and The Clorox Company since July 1, 2015. Mr. Fleischer served as a Director of Banner Corporation since October 2015 until December 1, 2016. He served as a Director of Banner Bank, a subsidiary of Banner Corporation since October 1, 2015 until December 1 2016. Mr. Fleischer served as a Director at AmericanWest Bank, Wilton Re Limited, Korn/Ferry International from 2002 to September 13, 2005, Advanced Career Technologies, Inc. and BearingPoint, Inc. from July 20, 2005 to July 15, 2008. He served as a Director of SteelPoint Technologies. He served as a Director of Milestone AV Technologies, Inc. since August 2003. Mr. Fleischer served as a Director of JonesTrading Institutional Services LLC. He served as a Member of the Advisory Board at CSE Capital, LLC. He has 35 years of financial and operational experience. Mr. Fleischer holds a M. Phil. in Management Studies from Oxford University, where he studied as a Rhodes Scholar and a B.A. degree, with honors, in Economics from the University of the Witwatersrand.Read Full Background




